name: fdb
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "fdb" %}
{% set version = "2.0.2" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: c10c54028308dcd3d5f5f3afe8a4039cbbef22dcd3b041c30b643cf2f0d33120

build:
  number: 0
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps --ignore-installed --no-cache-dir -vvv
  noarch: python

requirements:
  host:
    - python >=3.4
    - pip
  run:
    - python >=3.4
    - future >=0.16.0

test:
  imports:
    - fdb

about:
  home: https://www.firebirdsql.org/en/devel-python-driver/
  license: BSD
  license_family: BSD
  license_file: LICENSE.TXT
  summary: The Python driver for Firebird
  doc_url: http://fdb.readthedocs.io/en/v2.0/
  dev_url: https://github.com/FirebirdSQL/fdb

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - m-rossi
